DESCRIPTION	O
BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
1	O
.	O
Field	O
of	O
the	O
Invention	O
The	O
present	O
invention	O
generally	O
relates	O
to	O
wireless	O
communication	O
systems	O
and	O
,	O
more	O
particularly	O
,	O
to	O
a	O
voice	O
activity	O
detector	O
having	O
particular	O
application	O
to	O
mobile	O
radio	O
systems	O
,	O
such	O
a	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
systems	O
and	O
air-to-ground	O
telephony	O
,	O
for	O
the	O
detection	O
of	O
speech	O
in	O
noisy	O
environments	O
.	O

2	O
.	O
Description	O
of	O
the	O
Prior	O
Art	O
A	O
voice	O
activity	O
detector	O
(	O
VAD	O
)	O
is	O
used	O
to	O
detect	O
speech	O
for	O
applications	O
in	O
digital	O
speech	O
interpolation	O
(	O
DSI	O
)	O
and	O
noise	O
suppression	O
.	O
Accurate	O
voice	O
activity	O
detection	O
is	O
important	O
to	O
permit	O
reliable	O
detection	O
of	O
speech	O
in	O
a	O
noisy	O
environment	O
and	O
therefore	O
affects	O
system	O
performance	O
and	O
the	O
quality	O
of	O
the	O
received	O
speech	O
.	O
Prior	O
art	O
VAD	O
algorithms	O
which	O
analyze	O
spectral	O
properties	O
of	O
the	O
signal	O
suffer	O
from	O
high	O
computational	O
complexity	O
.	O
Simple	O
VAD	O
algorithms	O
which	O
look	O
at	O
short	O
term	O
time	O
characteristics	O
only	O
in	O
order	O
to	O
detect	O
speech	O
do	O
not	O
work	O
well	O
with	O
high	O
background	O
noise	O
.	O

There	O
are	O
basically	O
two	O
approaches	O
to	O
detecting	O
voice	O
activity	O
.	O
The	O
first	O
are	O
pattern	O
classifiers	O
which	O
use	O
spectral	O
characteristics	O
that	O
result	O
in	O
high	O
computational	O
complexity	O
.	O
An	O
example	O
of	O
this	O
approach	O
uses	O
five	O
different	O
measurements	O
on	O
the	O
speech	O
segment	O
to	O
be	O
classified	O
.	O
The	O
measured	O
parameters	O
are	O
the	O
zero-crossing	O
rate	O
,	O
the	O
speech	O
energy	O
,	O
the	O
correlation	O
between	O
adjacent	O
speech	O
samples	O
,	O
the	O
first	O
predictor	O
coefficient	O
from	O
a	O
12-pole	O
linear	O
predictive	O
coding	O
(	O
LPC	O
)	O
analysis	O
,	O
and	O
the	O
energy	O
in	O
the	O
prediction	O
error	O
.	O
This	O
speech	O
segment	O
is	O
assigned	O
to	O
a	O
particular	O
class	O
(	O
i	O
.	O
e	O
.	O
,	O
voiced	O
speech	O
,	O
un-voiced	O
speech	O
,	O
or	O
silence	O
)	O
based	O
on	O
a	O
minimum-distance	O
rule	O
obtained	O
under	O
the	O
assumption	O
that	O
the	O
measured	O
parameters	O
are	O
distributed	O
according	O
to	O
the	O
multidimensional	O
Gaussian	O
probability	O
density	O
function	O
.	O

The	O
second	O
approach	O
examines	O
the	O
time	O
domain	O
characteristics	O
of	O
speech	O
.	O
An	O
example	O
of	O
this	O
approach	O
implements	O
an	O
algorithm	O
that	O
uses	O
a	O
complementary	O
arrangement	O
of	O
the	O
level	O
,	O
envelope	O
slope	O
,	O
and	O
an	O
automatic	O
adaptive	O
zero	O
crossing	O
rate	O
detection	O
feature	O
to	O
provide	O
enhanced	O
noise	O
immunity	O
during	O
periods	O
of	O
high	O
system	O
noise	O
.	O

SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
It	O
is	O
therefore	O
an	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
voice	O
activity	O
detector	O
which	O
is	O
computationally	O
simple	O
yet	O
works	O
well	O
in	O
a	O
high	O
background	O
noise	O
environment	O
.	O

According	O
to	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
,	O
the	O
VAD	O
implements	O
a	O
simple	O
algorithm	O
that	O
is	O
able	O
to	O
adapt	O
to	O
the	O
background	O
noise	O
and	O
detect	O
speech	O
with	O
minimal	O
clipping	O
and	O
false	O
alarms	O
.	O
By	O
using	O
short	O
term	O
time	O
domain	O
parameters	O
to	O
discriminate	O
between	O
speech	O
and	O
silence	O
,	O
the	O
invention	O
is	O
able	O
to	O
adapt	O
to	O
background	O
noise	O
.	O
The	O
preferred	O
embodiment	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
is	O
implemented	O
in	O
a	O
CELP	O
coder	O
that	O
is	O
partitioned	O
into	O
parallel	O
tasks	O
for	O
real	O
time	O
implementation	O
on	O
dual	O
digital	O
signal	O
processors	O
(	O
DSPs	O
)	O
with	O
flexible	O
intertask	O
communication	O
,	O
prioritization	O
and	O
synchronization	O
with	O
asynchronous	O
transmit	O
and	O
receive	O
frame	O
timings	O
.	O
The	O
two	O
DSPs	O
are	O
used	O
in	O
a	O
master-slave	O
pair	O
.	O
Each	O
DSP	O
has	O
its	O
own	O
local	O
memory	O
.	O
The	O
DSPs	O
communicate	O
with	O
each	O
other	O
through	O
interrupts	O
.	O
Messages	O
are	O
passed	O
through	O
a	O
dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
.	O
Each	O
dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
has	O
separate	O
sections	O
for	O
command-response	O
and	O
for	O
data	O
.	O
While	O
both	O
DSPs	O
share	O
the	O
transmit	O
functions	O
,	O
the	O
slave	O
DSP	O
implements	O
receive	O
functions	O
including	O
echo	O
cancellation	O
,	O
voice	O
activity	O
detection	O
and	O
noise	O
suppression	O
.	O

