DETAILED	O
DESCRIPTION	O
OF	O
A	O
PREFERRED	O
EMBODIMENT	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
Referring	O
now	O
to	O
the	O
drawings	O
,	O
and	O
more	O
particularly	O
to	O
FIG	O
.	O
1	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
shown	O
a	O
block	O
diagram	O
of	O
the	O
architecture	O
of	O
the	O
CELP	O
coder	O
10	O
disclosed	O
in	O
application	O
Ser	O
.	O
No.	O
08/037	O
,	O
193	O
on	O
which	O
the	O
preferred	O
embodiment	O
of	O
how	O
the	O
invention	O
is	O
implemented	O
.	O
Two	O
DSPs	O
12	O
and	O
14	O
are	O
used	O
in	O
a	O
master-slave	O
pair	O
;	O
the	O
DSP	O
12	O
is	O
designated	O
the	O
master	O
,	O
and	O
DSP	O
14	O
is	O
the	O
slave	O
.	O
Each	O
DSP	O
12	O
and	O
14	O
has	O
its	O
own	O
local	O
memory	O
15	O
and	O
16	O
,	O
respectively	O
.	O
A	O
suitable	O
DSP	O
for	O
use	O
as	O
DSPs	O
12	O
and	O
14	O
is	O
the	O
Texas	O
Instruments	O
TMS320C31	O
DSP	O
.	O
The	O
DSPs	O
communicate	O
to	O
each	O
other	O
through	O
interrupts	O
.	O
Messages	O
are	O
passed	O
through	O
a	O
dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
18	O
.	O
Dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
18	O
has	O
separate	O
sections	O
for	O
command-response	O
and	O
for	O
data	O
.	O

The	O
main	O
computational	O
burden	O
for	O
the	O
speech	O
coder	O
is	O
adaptive	O
,	O
and	O
stochastic	O
code	O
book	O
searches	O
on	O
the	O
transmitter	O
and	O
is	O
shared	O
between	O
DSPs	O
12	O
and	O
14	O
.	O
DSP	O
12	O
implements	O
the	O
remaining	O
encoder	O
functions	O
.	O
All	O
the	O
speech	O
decoder	O
functions	O
are	O
implemented	O
on	O
DSP	O
14	O
.	O
Echo	O
canceler	O
and	O
noise	O
suppression	O
are	O
implemented	O
on	O
DSP	O
14	O
also	O
.	O

The	O
data	O
flow	O
through	O
the	O
DSPs	O
is	O
as	O
follows	O
for	O
the	O
transmit	O
side	O
.	O
DSP	O
14	O
collects	O
20	O
ms	O
of	O
.	O
mu	O
.	O
-	O
law	O
encoded	O
samples	O
and	O
converts	O
them	O
to	O
linear	O
values	O
.	O
These	O
samples	O
are	O
then	O
echo	O
canceled	O
and	O
passed	O
on	O
to	O
DSP	O
12	O
through	O
the	O
dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
18	O
.	O
The	O
LPC	O
(	O
Linear	O
Predictive	O
Coding	O
)	O
analysis	O
is	O
done	O
in	O
DSP	O
12	O
,	O
which	O
then	O
computes	O
CELP	O
vectors	O
for	O
each	O
subframe	O
and	O
transfers	O
it	O
to	O
DSP	O
14	O
over	O
the	O
dual	O
port	O
RAM	O
18	O
.	O
DSP	O
14	O
is	O
then	O
interrupted	O
and	O
assigned	O
the	O
task	O
to	O
compute	O
the	O
best	O
index	O
and	O
gain	O
for	O
the	O
second	O
half	O
of	O
the	O
codebook	O
.	O
DSP	O
12	O
computes	O
the	O
best	O
index	O
and	O
gain	O
for	O
the	O
first	O
half	O
of	O
the	O
codebook	O
and	O
chooses	O
between	O
the	O
two	O
based	O
on	O
the	O
match	O
score	O
.	O
DSP	O
12	O
also	O
updates	O
all	O
the	O
filter	O
states	O
at	O
the	O
end	O
of	O
each	O
subframe	O
and	O
computes	O
the	O
speech	O
parameters	O
for	O
transmission	O
.	O

Synchronization	O
is	O
maintained	O
by	O
giving	O
the	O
transmit	O
functions	O
higher	O
priority	O
over	O
receive	O
functions	O
.	O
Since	O
DSP	O
12	O
is	O
the	O
master	O
,	O
it	O
preempts	O
DSP	O
14	O
to	O
maintain	O
transmit	O
timing	O
.	O
DSP	O
14	O
executes	O
its	O
task	O
in	O
the	O
following	O
order	O
:	O
(	O
i	O
)	O
transmit	O
processing	O
,	O
(	O
ii	O
)	O
input	O
buffering	O
and	O
echo	O
cancellation	O
,	O
and	O
(	O
iii	O
)	O
receive	O
processing	O
and	O
voice	O
activity	O
detector	O
.	O

The	O
loading	O
of	O
the	O
DSPs	O
is	O
tabulated	O
in	O
Table	O
1	O
.	O

TABLE	O
1	O
______________________________________	O
