19	O
19	O
Load	O
95	O
%	O
95	O
%	O
______________________________________	O

It	O
is	O
the	O
third	O
(	O
iii	O
)	O
priority	O
of	O
DSP	O
14	O
tasks	O
to	O
which	O
the	O
subject	O
invention	O
is	O
directed	O
,	O
and	O
more	O
particularly	O
to	O
the	O
task	O
of	O
voice	O
activity	O
detection	O
.	O

For	O
the	O
successful	O
performance	O
of	O
the	O
voice	O
activity	O
detection	O
task	O
,	O
the	O
following	O
conditions	O
are	O
assumed	O
:	O
1	O
.	O
A	O
noise	O
canceling	O
microphone	O
with	O
close-talking	O
and	O
directional	O
properties	O
is	O
used	O
to	O
filter	O
high	O
background	O
noise	O
and	O
suppress	O
spurious	O
speech	O
.	O
This	O
guarantees	O
a	O
minimum	O
signal	O
to	O
noise	O
ratio	O
(	O
SNR	O
)	O
of	O
10	O
dB	O
.	O

2	O
.	O
An	O
echo	O
canceler	O
is	O
employed	O
to	O
suppress	O
any	O
feedback	O
occurring	O
either	O
due	O
to	O
use	O
of	O
speakerphones	O
or	O
acoustic	O
or	O
electrical	O
echoes	O
.	O

3	O
.	O
The	O
microphone	O
does	O
not	O
pick	O
up	O
any	O
mechanical	O
vibrations	O
.	O

Speech	O
sounds	O
can	O
be	O
divided	O
into	O
two	O
distinct	O
groups	O
based	O
on	O
the	O
mode	O
of	O
excitation	O
of	O
the	O
vocal	O
tract	O
:	O
Voiced	O
:	O
vowels	O
,	O
diphthongs	O
,	O
semivowels	O
,	O
voiced	O
stops	O
,	O
voiced	O
fricatives	O
,	O
and	O
nasals	O
.	O

Un-voiced	O
:	O
whispers	O
,	O
un-voiced	O
fricatives	O
,	O
and	O
un-voiced	O
stops	O
.	O

The	O
characteristics	O
of	O
these	O
two	O
groups	O
are	O
used	O
to	O
discriminate	O
between	O
speech	O
and	O
noise	O
.	O
The	O
background	O
noise	O
signal	O
is	O
assumed	O
to	O
change	O
slowly	O
when	O
compared	O
to	O
the	O
speech	O
signal	O
.	O

The	O
following	O
features	O
of	O
the	O
speech	O
signal	O
are	O
of	O
interest	O
:	O
Level--Voiced	O
speech	O
,	O
in	O
general	O
,	O
has	O
significantly	O
higher	O
energy	O
than	O
the	O
background	O
noise	O
except	O
for	O
onsets	O
and	O
decay	O
;	O
i	O
